<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Consumer Protection System">
  <data key="d0">Consumer Protection System</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Consumer Protection System is the primary legal framework referenced in the text, governing the definitions and regulations for consumer rights.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consumer Protection System is a regulatory framework aimed at protecting consumer rights and ensuring proper market performance.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a8154749b1feccbfe768628b4e18b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5921e285b202ad77baf19401a767f275</data>
  <data key="d4">مشروع_نظام_حماية_المستهلك</data>
  <data key="d5">1776813794</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Executive Regulations">
  <data key="d0">Executive Regulations</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Executive Regulations are the subordinate legal instruments that implement the Consumer Protection System.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a8154749b1feccbfe768628b4e18b60</data>
  <data key="d4">مشروع_نظام_حماية_المستهلك</data>
  <data key="d5">1776813786</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Competent Authority">
  <data key="d0">Competent Authority</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Competent Authority is a designated government body or regulatory entity empowered to oversee specific sectors, such as consumer protection, market surveillance, and strategic item controls, within its jurisdiction. Its primary mandate involves implementing systems, preparing and interpreting policies, and exercising jurisdiction over relevant regulations. The authority is responsible for issuing licenses for competitions, establishing operational rules, and designating strategic items, while also receiving mandatory reports from holders of such items.

In the realm of market oversight, the Competent Authority supervises execution, monitors market activities, and verifies compliance by economic operators. It holds the power to request necessary information from these operators, receive reports of non-compliance, and issue supervision rules to ensure adherence to standards. Furthermore, the authority has the capacity to assign or delegate market surveillance tasks to other entities as needed. To facilitate enforcement, the entity appoints inspectors, deciding on their appointment and associated rewards. Overall, it serves as the central regulatory organ ensuring legal and procedural integrity across various economic and protective domains.&lt;SEP&gt;The Competent Authority is the body responsible for supervising alternative dispute resolution providers and collaborating with the Ministry of Justice.&lt;SEP&gt;The Competent Authority is the entity responsible for defining requirements and procedures, acting in agreement with the Ministry of Justice.&lt;SEP&gt;The regulatory body or entity designated to receive and oversee activity reports from ADR providers.&lt;SEP&gt;The Competent Authority is responsible for defining procedures for representing consumers, alongside the Ministry of Justice.&lt;SEP&gt;An external body with which the Minister must coordinate when deciding to block the Electronic Premises.&lt;SEP&gt;The relevant authority responsible for coordinating the blocking of electronic premises.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a8154749b1feccbfe768628b4e18b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19ba78abd7c521789ac7c4a38d25114e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a6516eb7274d47a5878b05ae794d1f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2228f5a1f65a7fcad0b31452f9941e5d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d5f73112067d3017eacad446fe05c6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5dc591f6a06f37fe2f1b3209ca356c15&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1c5c3874985bccf0474e63d7c12c51d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-41f86c946795eb4b1b8e1172b283f83c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d72a2ff68ca9639d25fac0d200e648dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60f77fe5478de7b3d8b2672afe5ee95d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eba08bab139116de9ee95fe214a7f7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-da4dec7a272932b152bbbcd68d8fab88&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-db15b26408bc87ab744a17b5b0ea6317&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f5661f438c3dca334dc944b7a2eeeb87</data>
  <data key="d4">مشروع_نظام_حماية_المستهلك&lt;SEP&gt;نظام_التجارة_الإلكترونية</data>
  <data key="d5">1776814603</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Related Entities">
  <data key="d0">Related Entities</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Related Entities refer to any government bodies exercising authorities or tasks related to consumer protection and market monitoring.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a8154749b1feccbfe768628b4e18b60</data>
  <data key="d4">مشروع_نظام_حماية_المستهلك</data>
  <data key="d5">1776813786</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Consumer">
  <data key="d0">Consumer</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Consumer is defined as a natural person or individual entity who acts as the end recipient of goods, services, and related information to satisfy personal, family, or living needs. This role encompasses engaging in electronic commerce with service providers, accessing products offered by practitioners, and receiving statements regarding contract details. The Consumer’s status is primarily characterized by protected legal standing designed to balance power dynamics in commercial interactions, ensuring fair treatment, privacy, transparency, and equitable outcomes while shielding them from unfair contractual terms.

A central component of this protection is the right to comprehensive access to accurate and clear information. Economic Operators are obligated to provide prominent details regarding product attributes, prices, maintenance costs, terms, risks, and the availability of spare parts. Consumers are entitled to receive proof of purchase, such as an invoice, and may request copies of standard contracts without charge. Furthermore, operators must prove regulatory compliance, require explicit consent before conducting repairs, and respect the Consumer’s right to refuse electronic advertisements. In instances where an operator displays a price higher than intended, the Consumer is generally entitled to purchase at the lowest displayed price unless the error was unintentional. The Consumer also holds the right to know contract details through statements provided by the service provider.

Consumers possess significant rights regarding contract termination, warranties, and dispute resolution. They can cancel contracts signed outside business premises or entered into remotely within a specified period, often up to seven days, without providing reasons or bearing costs. If delivery is delayed, the Consumer may cancel and receive a refund. While protected, the Consumer bears the burden of proof for terminations and may be liable for product loss under specific conditions, though liability for errors exists only if caused by incorrect operator instructions. Statutory warranties apply regardless of additional warranties, and the Consumer retains the right to file complaints and seek remedies for violations. Providers must declare how these dispute resolution rights (waiver, binding nature, enforceability) apply. Disputes may be settled directly, handled via minor claims procedures, or resolved through alternative means.

Additionally, the Consumer is safeguarded by regulatory measures that include receiving warnings and benefiting from product suspensions. Their personal data and electronic communications are handled by Service Providers, requiring strict protection of privacy and explicit consent for usage or disclosure. The Consumer is recognized as an individual who may make errors in electronic correspondence and is one of the primary parties involved in disputes. Ultimately, the Consumer is the protected party who benefits from these systemic regulations, ensuring effective legal recourse against operator violations and securing transparent, fair commercial transactions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consumer is the recipient of goods or services who receives the invoice from the Service Provider.&lt;SEP&gt;Consumer is the target audience of electronic advertisements, who must be protected from deception and misinformation.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consumer is the party granted the right to cancel contracts within seven days under specific conditions.&lt;SEP&gt;The Consumer is the individual purchasing goods or services, entitled to specific protections under Article Fourteen.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a8154749b1feccbfe768628b4e18b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5921e285b202ad77baf19401a767f275&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23f16ba22036bb88da1664b390f68ca1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbb3cd60b4bd30c2e1383463af5924c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bea1774b99d54deb70d6648484455df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-757265b902decbf8c55e1b070565644a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-08494eb61cc41dcbd344a3b581092bcd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eba8035888adcd130040e9dbfd9a13d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d0188b6660d92e46d97b6aa5ddfa898&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9acf77028a44df007ff93e9e4464a66e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c85a7dbe91de94e3f41746b161dffff2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-811c2282e5faf0e8745c51115a8604e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb2c83cde8c36de94f7057d58fb2869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c71f72d143d12f0695043e4deb70f183&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec82bc886475d035ec952d60da6a6e6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05ecf93d1d9a52151af2a72301234ed7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1db2fdbafbec4cf6444dec6b72a0824e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10fae82f7c6a76b4dbf01080c7ed22eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e82925b2fc83bb4036c3b1f007ba923&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfe11211e281ef2abb48c30415b14f61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a056e5bd9daa08695b5a665b53f6d3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d152ef32e10dd0dd90a99794e2ce09a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23ea8c91412652822b5737482cd0f932&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-294b2d78155c5479740e5f6e60fabd5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93b8a69d3470d8fd4caae59080df0a54&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ee11e2f2efdecd0a6233d3dde78ac94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47f120917e5636d314c4a5e75774c7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-301a4ffbdfd6fdb0a956239d0553872e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bc991839dd0cc98acaf12ea5bc58ecc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-019c5b0704e7195269616af2f7e331e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4d1807f1fc70cd86f3926044c5b150a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbcbc9c6d4024ed107a3aed8073f87c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70049c2c9beee67be467a0bc1e8e5319&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3ef01cc61802e9c5898cf34fea5a1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c81dd10f0ce67f495fcaa4afb41ade53&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d15616980ad303389944137db1af4f22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbdc0bdfb37532b71f5f2a12cb9f8fe0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7675218c2feb4f3d03df5d15f853c435&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0bb91dbf0d0d74be15a1f23f7ef09d39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1c5c3874985bccf0474e63d7c12c51d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2e9d4353bb95f7bca809f541cd54320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e40f0555a179abb24172277f52bec711&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b54adc716da8570bddd8c2bd41899a6f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8eba08bab139116de9ee95fe214a7f7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51ea5244ed2d72532c1d4e4a8c7c8711&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc0c7efa3b63af90af17dc69c2eb4ab7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9b912e56726cb9e0d5237d61584a5fa6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ef5c3f67882b7588927d8bca42047269&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30e605d9deb7e33ed48fcf51264fb16e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b0f30d8785ebf55f768a527b1ede688f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4385a57314892c443871db0108ea1b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7dce39ad69ab952b0a24c9573b89731d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98520f83d72a9bac06aacc6991d7d823&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c0d47d22075e87911525f2b1b1a29585</data>
  <data key="d4">مشروع_نظام_حماية_المستهلك&lt;SEP&gt;نظام_التجارة_الإلكترونية</data>
