  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Economic Operator">
  <data key="d0">Economic Operator</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Economic Operator is a natural or legal person, public or private, engaged in commercial, industrial, professional, or craft activities within the Kingdom. Serving as the primary market participant and legally accountable party for product and service delivery, this entity supplies goods or services to consumers through various channels, including electronic means and remote contracts. As the central business counterpart, the Economic Operator functions as the responsible party for ensuring regulatory compliance, transparency, ethical conduct, and robust consumer protection. This role mandates that products or services meet established standards, specifications, quality criteria, and other requirements, while also bearing the burden of proving fulfillment of all informational obligations.

A core aspect of the Economic Operator’s duties involves strict adherence to regulatory standards regarding transparency and accurate pricing. The operator must display prices clearly and prominently, prohibiting different prices for identical items unless due to unintentional error, and must disclose specific information when reducing prices. They are obligated to provide clear, understandable, and complete information to the consumer before entering into any remote contract, particularly for contracts concluded outside business premises. This includes disclosing identity data, mandatory pre-contractual details, and specific product information. Ethical standards prohibit unfair commercial practices and terms, such as liability exemptions or unilateral modification rights. Furthermore, the operator is responsible for preparing standard contracts, issuing invoices, providing copies upon request, and ensuring proper handling of consumer data with special attention to vulnerable consumers. They must also notify competent authorities about product or service non-compliance and provide information about other operators involved.

Regarding liability and warranty obligations, the Economic Operator is liable for the loss of a product until delivery and is responsible for delivering it to the consumer. They must notify consumers of any delays and are specifically obligated to accept returned products and process refunds within fourteen days of notification of contract termination. The operator must inform consumers of their right to cancel contracts concluded outside business premises. While services are generally provided free of charge, operators may charge for price offer preparation if informed beforehand and must apply for licenses and provide details before starting competitions. Additionally, the Economic Operator provides statutory warranties to consumers and may supply digital content or services bundled with products, which can affect warranty applicability. In cases of remote contracts, the Economic Operator must be notified in writing of any termination.

Regarding warranty specifics, the Economic Operator is the entity responsible towards the consumer for any breach of product or service warranty within specified timeframes. Specifically, the entity is responsible for repairing, replacing, or refunding products when a statutory warranty is breached. The entity responsible for the product may bear liability for assembly errors under specific contractual or instructional conditions. Moreover, the Economic Operator is an entity permitted to offer additional warranties to consumers alongside statutory warranties, required to provide clear documentation and identify the warranty as "additional." The operator is also the entity legally obligated to provide spare parts and maintenance services and inform consumers of the relevant duration. Under Article 56, the Economic Operator is an entity obligated to notify consumers regarding spare part availability timelines. By integrating regulatory adherence, informational accuracy, and ethical duties, the Economic Operator maintains high standards of honesty and respect for consumer rights.

From a regulatory oversight perspective, the Economic Operator is the business entity subject to inspection, required to provide documents, data, and access to premises and vehicles. It is identified by name, ID, commercial registry number, tax number, and address. The Economic Operator is the entity subject to inspection and potential administrative penalties for violating regulations or laws. It is an entity subject to administrative penalties and holds the right to object to such penalties as outlined in the text. The Economic Operator is a business entity that may be subject to legal actions for non-compliant practices and can seek court orders to stop such practices. The Economic Operator is an entity responsible for compliance with regulations; actions violating these rules can cause harm to consumers. Finally, the Economic Operator is the other primary party involved in disputes with consumers, subject to simplified judicial review.&lt;SEP&gt;The Economic Operator is a business entity involved in commercial transactions with consumers, subject to dispute resolution mechanisms.&lt;SEP&gt;An economic operator is a party subject to the regulations, who may commit violations and is obligated to correct them under threat of corrective measures.&lt;SEP&gt;An Economic Operator is an entity subject to administrative penalties if they violate the provisions of the system and regulations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-7a8154749b1feccbfe768628b4e18b60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5921e285b202ad77baf19401a767f275&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23f16ba22036bb88da1664b390f68ca1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-19ba78abd7c521789ac7c4a38d25114e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dbb3cd60b4bd30c2e1383463af5924c9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bea1774b99d54deb70d6648484455df9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-757265b902decbf8c55e1b070565644a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-eba8035888adcd130040e9dbfd9a13d6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-929aeab810b6ef4b56bb0ac1266d349f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2d0188b6660d92e46d97b6aa5ddfa898&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9acf77028a44df007ff93e9e4464a66e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c85a7dbe91de94e3f41746b161dffff2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-811c2282e5faf0e8745c51115a8604e5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6fb2c83cde8c36de94f7057d58fb2869&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a9356ec391f6d77e79bbb8d92e8e7958&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c71f72d143d12f0695043e4deb70f183&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec82bc886475d035ec952d60da6a6e6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9a6516eb7274d47a5878b05ae794d1f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb13f1b3abd5cc99dd565ac09795ffc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05ecf93d1d9a52151af2a72301234ed7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-10fae82f7c6a76b4dbf01080c7ed22eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6e82925b2fc83bb4036c3b1f007ba923&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dfe11211e281ef2abb48c30415b14f61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4a056e5bd9daa08695b5a665b53f6d3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-23ea8c91412652822b5737482cd0f932&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-294b2d78155c5479740e5f6e60fabd5b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-93b8a69d3470d8fd4caae59080df0a54&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ee11e2f2efdecd0a6233d3dde78ac94&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c47f120917e5636d314c4a5e75774c7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-301a4ffbdfd6fdb0a956239d0553872e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-019c5b0704e7195269616af2f7e331e2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a4d1807f1fc70cd86f3926044c5b150a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c6572d1610f6bb7f6ec41fc6f8eb934f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6d5f73112067d3017eacad446fe05c6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5086b6cf9bc02c27ea5fb4cb9ed609ed&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-70049c2c9beee67be467a0bc1e8e5319&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b3ef01cc61802e9c5898cf34fea5a1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c81dd10f0ce67f495fcaa4afb41ade53&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d15616980ad303389944137db1af4f22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4f2ea9e729aab0deda37682e004b3fc6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bbdc0bdfb37532b71f5f2a12cb9f8fe0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7675218c2feb4f3d03df5d15f853c435&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0bb91dbf0d0d74be15a1f23f7ef09d39&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1c5c3874985bccf0474e63d7c12c51d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3180421cdd22a4773c6db6e08f304f90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1c88be299a43d67d9b9fc0d255ce74ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4761261f928e9e2a04c5cf880b36af44&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6a6d5fd04ff86c2506f73df9e65d57b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2e9d4353bb95f7bca809f541cd54320&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e40f0555a179abb24172277f52bec711&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b54adc716da8570bddd8c2bd41899a6f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51ea5244ed2d72532c1d4e4a8c7c8711&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c473b635efc04ff40f299b6d7f6fc2db</data>
